				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$L_b$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M12"><mml:msub><mml:mi>L</mml:mi><mml:mi>b</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2024_5711_Article_IEq6.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> CpG sites. Following Libby and Novick [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR25">25</xref>], we define <inline-formula id="IEq7"><alternatives><tex-math id="M13">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
